{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"So you probably have the sense,\nas most people do,"},{"time":3840,"text":"that polarization\nis getting worse in our country,"},{"time":7520,"text":"that the divide\nbetween the left and the right"},{"time":11000,"text":"is as bad as it's been\nin really any of our lifetimes."},{"time":14560,"text":"But you might also reasonably wonder\nif research backs up your intuition."},{"time":20560,"text":"And in a nutshell,\nthe answer is sadly yes."},{"time":26920,"text":"In study after study, we find"},{"time":28960,"text":"that liberals and conservatives\nhave grown further apart."},{"time":33440,"text":"They increasingly wall themselves off\nin these ideological silos,"},{"time":38240,"text":"consuming different news,\ntalking only to like-minded others"},{"time":42400,"text":"and more and more choosing\nto live in different parts of the country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46720,"text":"And I think that\nmost alarming of all of it"},{"time":49960,"text":"is seeing this rising\nanimosity on both sides."},{"time":54440,"text":"Liberals and conservatives,"},{"time":56120,"text":"Democrats and Republicans,"},{"time":58040,"text":"more and more they just\ndon't like one another."},{"time":62320,"text":"You see it in many different ways."},{"time":64360,"text":"They don't want to befriend one another.\nThey don't want to date one another."},{"time":68040,"text":"If they do, if they find out,\nthey find each other less attractive,"},{"time":71360,"text":"and they more and more don't want\ntheir children to marry someone"},{"time":74480,"text":"who supports the other party,"},{"time":76200,"text":"a particularly shocking statistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79640,"text":"You know, in my lab,\nthe students that I work with,"},{"time":82480,"text":"we're talking about\nsome sort of social pattern --"},{"time":85960,"text":"I'm a movie buff, and so I'm often like,"},{"time":89520,"text":"what kind of movie are we in here\nwith this pattern?"},{"time":93080,"text":"So what kind of movie are we in\nwith political polarization?"},{"time":97080,"text":"Well, it could be a disaster movie."},{"time":100880,"text":"It certainly seems like a disaster."},{"time":102920,"text":"Could be a war movie."},{"time":105640,"text":"Also fits."},{"time":107480,"text":"But what I keep thinking is that\nwe're in a zombie apocalypse movie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":112800,"text":"Right? You know the kind."},{"time":115120,"text":"There's people wandering around in packs,"},{"time":117560,"text":"not thinking for themselves,"},{"time":119360,"text":"seized by this mob mentality"},{"time":121000,"text":"trying to spread their disease\nand destroy society."},{"time":125480,"text":"And you probably think, as I do,"},{"time":127840,"text":"that you're the good guy\nin the zombie apocalypse movie,"},{"time":131320,"text":"and all this hate and polarization,\nit's being propagated by the other people,"},{"time":135040,"text":"because we're Brad Pitt, right?"},{"time":137760,"text":"Free-thinking, righteous,"},{"time":140680,"text":"just trying to hold on\nto what we hold dear,"},{"time":143000,"text":"you know, not foot soldiers\nin the army of the undead."},{"time":146600,"text":"Not that."},{"time":148080,"text":"Never that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150080,"text":"But here's the thing:"},{"time":151600,"text":"what movie do you suppose\nthey think they're in?"},{"time":155480,"text":"Right?"},{"time":156720,"text":"Well, they absolutely think\nthat they're the good guys"},{"time":159280,"text":"in the zombie apocalypse movie. Right?"},{"time":161160,"text":"And you'd better believe\nthat they think that they're Brad Pitt"},{"time":164160,"text":"and that we, we are the zombies."},{"time":169120,"text":"And who's to say that they're wrong?"},{"time":172440,"text":"I think that the truth is\nthat we're all a part of this."},{"time":176240,"text":"And the good side of that\nis that we can be a part of the solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180280,"text":"So what are we going to do?"},{"time":183320,"text":"What can we do to chip away\nat polarization in everyday life?"},{"time":187600,"text":"What could we do to connect with\nand communicate with"},{"time":191440,"text":"our political counterparts?"},{"time":193720,"text":"Well, these were exactly the questions\nthat I and my colleague, Matt Feinberg,"},{"time":197880,"text":"became fascinated with a few years ago,"},{"time":199762,"text":"and we started\ndoing research on this topic."},{"time":202920,"text":"And one of the first things\nthat we discovered"},{"time":205920,"text":"that I think is really helpful\nfor understanding polarization"},{"time":209400,"text":"is to understand"},{"time":210640,"text":"that the political divide in our country\nis undergirded by a deeper moral divide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215080,"text":"So one of the most robust findings\nin the history of political psychology"},{"time":219880,"text":"is this pattern identified\nby Jon Haidt and Jesse Graham,"},{"time":223600,"text":"psychologists,"},{"time":224840,"text":"that liberals and conservatives\ntend to endorse different values"},{"time":228880,"text":"to different degrees."},{"time":230600,"text":"So for example, we find that liberals\ntend to endorse values like equality"},{"time":236120,"text":"and fairness and care\nand protection from harm"},{"time":239800,"text":"more than conservatives do."},{"time":241960,"text":"And conservatives tend to endorse\nvalues like loyalty, patriotism,"},{"time":247240,"text":"respect for authority and moral purity"},{"time":250720,"text":"more than liberals do."},{"time":253920,"text":"And Matt and I were thinking\nthat maybe this moral divide"},{"time":258000,"text":"might be helpful\nfor understanding how it is"},{"time":261120,"text":"that liberals and conservatives\ntalk to one another"},{"time":263560,"text":"and why they so often\nseem to talk past one another"},{"time":266000,"text":"when they do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267240,"text":"So we conducted a study"},{"time":269240,"text":"where we recruited liberals to a study"},{"time":272360,"text":"where they were supposed\nto write a persuasive essay"},{"time":274840,"text":"that would be compelling to a conservative\nin support of same-sex marriage."},{"time":279800,"text":"And what we found was that liberals\ntended to make arguments"},{"time":283080,"text":"in terms of the liberal moral values\nof equality and fairness."},{"time":287280,"text":"So they said things like,"},{"time":289040,"text":"\"Everyone should have the right\nto love whoever they choose,\""},{"time":292440,"text":"and, \"They\" -- they being gay Americans --"},{"time":295040,"text":"\"deserve the same equal rights\nas other Americans.\""},{"time":298360,"text":"Overall, we found\nthat 69 percent of liberals"},{"time":301600,"text":"invoked one of the more liberal\nmoral values in constructing their essay,"},{"time":307040,"text":"and only nine percent invoked\none of the more conservative moral values,"},{"time":310760,"text":"even though they were supposed\nto be trying to persuade conservatives."},{"time":314200,"text":"And when we studied conservatives\nand had them make persuasive arguments"},{"time":318520,"text":"in support of making English\nthe official language of the US,"},{"time":321440,"text":"a classically conservative\npolitical position,"},{"time":324000,"text":"we found that they weren't\nmuch better at this."},{"time":326240,"text":"59 percent of them made arguments"},{"time":327880,"text":"in terms of one of the more\nconservative moral values,"},{"time":330600,"text":"and just eight percent\ninvoked a liberal moral value,"},{"time":333120,"text":"even though they were supposed\nto be targeting liberals for persuasion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337480,"text":"Now, you can see right away\nwhy we're in trouble here. Right?"},{"time":342280,"text":"People's moral values,\nthey're their most deeply held beliefs."},{"time":345800,"text":"People are willing\nto fight and die for their values."},{"time":349720,"text":"Why are they going to give that up\njust to agree with you"},{"time":352440,"text":"on something that they don't particularly\nwant to agree with you on anyway?"},{"time":356000,"text":"If that persuasive appeal that\nyou're making to your Republican uncle"},{"time":359280,"text":"means that he doesn't\njust have to change his view,"},{"time":361720,"text":"he's got to change\nhis underlying values, too,"},{"time":363910,"text":"that's not going to go very far."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366080,"text":"So what would work better?"},{"time":368200,"text":"Well, we believe it's a technique\nthat we call moral reframing,"},{"time":372520,"text":"and we've studied it\nin a series of experiments."},{"time":375160,"text":"In one of these experiments,"},{"time":376680,"text":"we recruited liberals\nand conservatives to a study"},{"time":379840,"text":"where they read one of three essays"},{"time":382160,"text":"before having their environmental\nattitudes surveyed."},{"time":385640,"text":"And the first of these essays"},{"time":387160,"text":"was a relatively conventional\npro-environmental essay"},{"time":390560,"text":"that invoked the liberal values\nof care and protection from harm."},{"time":394600,"text":"It said things like,\n\"In many important ways"},{"time":397160,"text":"we are causing real harm\nto the places we live in,\""},{"time":400000,"text":"and, \"It is essential\nthat we take steps now"},{"time":402840,"text":"to prevent further destruction\nfrom being done to our Earth.\""},{"time":407120,"text":"Another group of participants"},{"time":408560,"text":"were assigned to read\na really different essay"},{"time":410800,"text":"that was designed to tap into\nthe conservative value of moral purity."},{"time":416190,"text":"It was a pro-environmental essay as well,"},{"time":418200,"text":"and it said things like,"},{"time":419720,"text":"\"Keeping our forests, drinking water,\nand skies pure is of vital importance.\""},{"time":425000,"text":"\"We should regard the pollution"},{"time":426520,"text":"of the places we live in\nto be disgusting.\""},{"time":429160,"text":"And, \"Reducing pollution\ncan help us preserve"},{"time":431280,"text":"what is pure and beautiful\nabout the places we live.\""},{"time":435880,"text":"And then we had a third group"},{"time":437320,"text":"that were assigned\nto read just a nonpolitical essay."},{"time":439840,"text":"It was just a comparison group\nso we could get a baseline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442600,"text":"And what we found when we surveyed people"},{"time":444577,"text":"about their environmental\nattitudes afterwards,"},{"time":446800,"text":"we found that liberals,\nit didn't matter what essay they read."},{"time":449760,"text":"They tended to have highly\npro-environmental attitudes regardless."},{"time":452880,"text":"Liberals are on board\nfor environmental protection."},{"time":455320,"text":"Conservatives, however,"},{"time":456560,"text":"were significantly more supportive\nof progressive environmental policies"},{"time":461000,"text":"and environmental protection"},{"time":462560,"text":"if they had read the moral purity essay"},{"time":464640,"text":"than if they read\none of the other two essays."},{"time":468160,"text":"We even found that conservatives\nwho read the moral purity essay"},{"time":471280,"text":"were significantly more likely to say\nthat they believed in global warming"},{"time":474800,"text":"and were concerned about global warming,"},{"time":476729,"text":"even though this essay\ndidn't even mention global warming."},{"time":479480,"text":"That's just a related environmental issue."},{"time":481960,"text":"But that's how robust\nthis moral reframing effect was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485960,"text":"And we've studied this on a whole slew\nof different political issues."},{"time":489720,"text":"So if you want to move conservatives"},{"time":493480,"text":"on issues like same-sex marriage\nor national health insurance,"},{"time":496600,"text":"it helps to tie these liberal\npolitical issues to conservative values"},{"time":500080,"text":"like patriotism and moral purity."},{"time":503800,"text":"And we studied it the other way, too."},{"time":505920,"text":"If you want to move liberals\nto the right on conservative policy issues"},{"time":509760,"text":"like military spending and making English\nthe official language of the US,"},{"time":514400,"text":"you're going to be more persuasive"},{"time":516080,"text":"if you tie those conservative\npolicy issues to liberal moral values"},{"time":519440,"text":"like equality and fairness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522640,"text":"All these studies\nhave the same clear message:"},{"time":525520,"text":"if you want to persuade\nsomeone on some policy,"},{"time":528480,"text":"it's helpful to connect that policy\nto their underlying moral values."},{"time":533520,"text":"And when you say it like that"},{"time":535720,"text":"it seems really obvious. Right?"},{"time":537240,"text":"Like, why did we come here tonight?"},{"time":539040,"text":"Why --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":540280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":541840,"text":"It's incredibly intuitive."},{"time":545400,"text":"And even though it is,\nit's something we really struggle to do."},{"time":548720,"text":"You know, it turns out that when we go\nto persuade somebody on a political issue,"},{"time":552600,"text":"we talk like we're speaking into a mirror."},{"time":555360,"text":"We don't persuade so much\nas we rehearse our own reasons"},{"time":559760,"text":"for why we believe\nsome sort of political position."},{"time":563400,"text":"We kept saying when we were designing\nthese reframed moral arguments,"},{"time":567840,"text":"\"Empathy and respect,\nempathy and respect.\""},{"time":571040,"text":"If you can tap into that,"},{"time":572520,"text":"you can connect"},{"time":574200,"text":"and you might be able to persuade\nsomebody in this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577560,"text":"So thinking again"},{"time":580000,"text":"about what movie we're in,"},{"time":583200,"text":"maybe I got carried away before."},{"time":584800,"text":"Maybe it's not a zombie apocalypse movie."},{"time":587520,"text":"Maybe instead it's a buddy cop movie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590040,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":592080,"text":"Just roll with it, just go with it please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":596480,"text":"You know the kind:\nthere's a white cop and a black cop,"},{"time":599200,"text":"or maybe a messy cop and an organized cop."},{"time":601360,"text":"Whatever it is, they don't get along"},{"time":603440,"text":"because of this difference."},{"time":605520,"text":"But in the end, when they have\nto come together and they cooperate,"},{"time":608760,"text":"the solidarity that they feel,"},{"time":610720,"text":"it's greater because of that gulf\nthat they had to cross. Right?"},{"time":615280,"text":"And remember that in these movies,"},{"time":617280,"text":"it's usually worst in the second act"},{"time":620200,"text":"when our leads are further apart\nthan ever before."},{"time":623440,"text":"And so maybe that's\nwhere we are in this country,"},{"time":625800,"text":"late in the second act\nof a buddy cop movie --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":628000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":630600,"text":"torn apart but about\nto come back together."},{"time":635400,"text":"It sounds good,"},{"time":637080,"text":"but if we want it to happen,"},{"time":638960,"text":"I think the responsibility\nis going to start with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642520,"text":"So this is my call to you:"},{"time":645480,"text":"let's put this country back together."},{"time":649080,"text":"Let's do it despite the politicians"},{"time":652160,"text":"and the media and Facebook and Twitter"},{"time":655040,"text":"and Congressional redistricting"},{"time":656600,"text":"and all of it,\nall the things that divide us."},{"time":660360,"text":"Let's do it because it's right."},{"time":663920,"text":"And let's do it\nbecause this hate and contempt"},{"time":668360,"text":"that flows through all of us every day"},{"time":671400,"text":"makes us ugly and it corrupts us,"},{"time":674600,"text":"and it threatens\nthe very fabric of our society."},{"time":679960,"text":"We owe it to one another and our country"},{"time":682640,"text":"to reach out and try to connect."},{"time":686000,"text":"We can't afford to hate them any longer,"},{"time":690200,"text":"and we can't afford\nto let them hate us either."},{"time":693880,"text":"Empathy and respect."},{"time":695880,"text":"Empathy and respect."},{"time":697920,"text":"If you think about it, it's the very least\nthat we owe our fellow citizens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702400,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703640,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}